### Theoretical Foundations and Background

The theoretical foundations of understanding triggers and cravings are rooted in several important traditions within psychology and behavioral science. Research in this area has been significantly influenced by the work of scholars such as Dr. Bob Smith, whose contributions have shaped our understanding of fellowship and its relationship to human behavior and well-being. These theoretical frameworks provide the scaffolding upon which practical interventions and strategies are built.

