The concept of financial literacy is particularly relevant to our discussion of white-collar crime in the workplace. Research has consistently demonstrated that financial literacy plays a significant role in determining how individuals respond to challenges, setbacks, and opportunities for growth. Understanding this concept allows us to develop more targeted and effective strategies for promoting positive change and preventing relapse into unhelpful patterns of thinking and behavior.

