The concept of ethical decision-making is particularly relevant to our discussion of the legal consequences of financial crime. Research has consistently demonstrated that ethical decision-making plays a significant role in determining how individuals respond to challenges, setbacks, and opportunities for growth. Understanding this concept allows us to develop more targeted and effective strategies for promoting positive change and preventing relapse into unhelpful patterns of thinking and behavior.

