### Theoretical Foundations and Background

The theoretical foundations of interview skills and professional presentation are rooted in several important traditions within psychology and behavioral science. Research in this area has been significantly influenced by the work of scholars such as Dr. Angela Duckworth, whose contributions have shaped our understanding of communication skills and its relationship to human behavior and well-being. These theoretical frameworks provide the scaffolding upon which practical interventions and strategies are built.

