The first essential concept is the relationship between financial literacy and communication skills. These two elements are deeply interconnected, and understanding their relationship is crucial for developing effective strategies for change. When individuals develop a clearer understanding of how financial literacy influences their experience, they become better able to intervene at key points in the cycle of thought, emotion, and behavior. This awareness is the foundation upon which all other skills and strategies are built.

